    <section/>
    <section>
      <title/>
      <indexterm>Translation Memory<indexterm>merging</indexterm></indexterm>
      <indexterm>merging<indexterm><keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmems"
          /></indexterm></indexterm>
      <p>If several translators are working on a large document, each of them uses and updates a
        separate <keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmem"/>.</p>
      <p>For the translation of subsequent releases of the document, it is useful to merge these to
        create a single consolidated <keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmem"
        />.</p>
      <p>You can merge <keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmems"/> in two ways: <ul>
          <li>While importing an external <keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmem"
            /> (see <xref href="xlmimp.dita#xlmimp"/>).</li>
          <li>By merging two internal <keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmems"
            />.</li>
        </ul></p>
      <p>The merging of two <keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmems"/> is
        described using two sample names, <codeph>TMEM01</codeph> and <codeph>TMEM02</codeph>.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Prerequisites</title>
      <ul>
        <li>The two <keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmems"/> to be merged must
          exist.</li>
        <li>They must have the same source language.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Calling sequence</title>
      <p>Select: <ol>
          <li>The <q>Translation Memory List</q> window</li>
          <li>The <keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmem"/> to be merged, for
            example, <codeph>TMEM01</codeph></li>
          <li>Select <b>Mergeâ€¦</b> from the <b>File</b> menu</li>
        </ol></p>
      <p>The <q>Merge Translation Memory</q> window (see <xref href="#xlmmrg/mergexlmwin"/>) is
        displayed. <required-cleanup><indexterm>windows<indexterm>Merge <keyword
                conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmem"
        /></indexterm></indexterm></required-cleanup><fig id="mergexlmwin" expanse="column">
          <title>Merge <keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmem"/>
            window</title><image placement="break" href="eqfb7s9f.gif"><alt>Figure shows Merge
              window</alt></image></fig>
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Options and parameters</title>
      <p>The <b>Into <keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmem"/></b> list box
        displays all available <keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmems"/>. Select
        the <keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmem"/>, for example
          <codeph>TMEM02</codeph>, into which to merge the previously selected <keyword
          conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmem"/>
        <codeph>TMEM01</codeph>.</p>
      <p>When you have selected the target <keyword
          conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmem"/>, click <b>Merge</b> to begin merging
        the <keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmems"/>. </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Results</title>
      <p>The contents of <codeph>TMEM01</codeph> is merged into the target <keyword
          conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmem"/>
        <codeph>TMEM02</codeph>. The <keyword conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmem"/>
        <codeph>TMEM01</codeph> remains unchanged. You can begin to use the extended <keyword
          conref="common-symbols.dita#common-symbols/xlmem"/>
        <codeph>TMEM02</codeph>.</p>
    </section>
